*    [Is that it?] So much has transpired, but it almost feels like you can see a million loose ends spooling off the sakura boughs and trailing everywhere in all directions.
-
    It is a sad fact of life, but poring through the committee planning documents for catching up granted you insight into a whole world of fest-running.
    
    The Spring Festival this year, amazing as it is, turned out to be closer to 50-60% of what the committee had meticulously planned out.
    
    From their notes, little stickies and white-outs and scratch-ins, you could tell that a lot of passion was poured into these dead ends.
    
    There is always so much that will inevitably be left on the table with any event of this scale.
    
    It's not the end of the world. Nobody can say this festival wasn't a success. Ideas can be recycled.
    
    Better to move on to next incredible thing.
    
*   And yet[...], there's always that sense of unavoidable loss. Next year will come, with new faces and opportunities. 
-
