    ... 
    
    Already, the memories of those threads are fading.
    
    Not the encounters themselves, but the lingering sense of loss at seeing them unwind into places you cannot follow.
    
    There are worlds where you got to understand different members of the committee in different ways.
    
    There are countless alternate climaxes and denouments.
    
    You have lost nothing by not being in those worlds. Just existing here, in this moment, talking to me like this, is proof that you have won.
    
    There are so many more where you gave up. 
    
    You stopped talking to the committee, you let the day slide by, and you never saw any of the millions of small miracles of the festival unfold.
    
    Moreover, the committee would have been too busy and engrossed in their existing dynamics to go out of their way to change anything.
    
    Simply by virtue of existing and caring for others, this impossibly rare form of healing is accessible to you, honey.
    
    You won.
    
    Let that sink in.
    
    You won.
    
    
